<HEADLINE> Pak President, Chief Executive Greet Indian Counterparts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani President Rafiq
Tarar has greeted Indian President Raman Narayanan on the occasion
of India's Independence Day falling on August 15, reported the
Associated Press of Pakistan (APP) Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In his message, Tarar said, "Excellency, I have the pleasure to
convey to you and the Indian people our greetings on the occasion
of the Independence Day of the Republic of India."
</P>
<P>
General Pervez Musharraf, Chief Executive of Pakistan, has also
greeted Indian Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee on the same
occasion, APP said.
</P>
<P>
Despite hostilities existing between Pakistan and India, the
two South Asian countries regularly exchanged greetings on the
other's independence days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
