<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Afghan Warlord Deserts Taliban to Rejoin Opposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 15 (Xinhua) -- A powerful Afghan warlord, who
defected to the ruling Taliban militia in April, rejoined the
opposition ranks over the weekend, the Afghan Islamic Press (AIP)
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah Jan Wahidi's desertion along with hundreds of his
supporters can create serious problem for the Taliban in the
northeastern province of Laghman which he dominated, the Pakistan-
based agency said.
</P>
<P>
Laghman borders the province of Kabul where the national
capital of the same name is located. 
</P>
</TEXT>
