<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Seizes 191 Kilograms of Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Anti Narcotics
Force in a combing operation in the southwestern Balochistan
province seized 191 kilograms of heroin from Brabchah on Pak-
Afghan border Monday, says a press release issued here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The drugs are being manufactured in Chotto in Helmand Province
of Afghanistan and brought to border area of Pakistan and shifted
to other outlets either to Iran or through coast, the release said.
</P>
<P>
The price of the heroin seized in Monday's operation is 19
million U.S. dollars, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
