<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 88,000 EU Citizens Register for Belgium's Local Vote </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Belgium has received more than
88,000 applications for voting in its local elections from a
total of nearly 499,000 nationals of other European Union member
states who live in the country, the Belgian Interior Ministry said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In June, Interior Minister Antoine Duquesne expected some 45,
000 of them to register for the local vote scheduled for October 8.
</P>
<P>
The people from other EU member countries living in Belgium
were requested to register before the July 31 deadline so that,
for the first time, they can get the right to take part in the
local elections.
</P>
<P>
However, the registered foreign voters would be viewed as
violating the Belgian law if they finally fail to vote.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that more than half of the registered foreign
voters are Italians. The other large groups are French and Dutch
nationals.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
