<DOCNO> XIE20000816.0006 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mongolian President Stresses Ties With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian President Nachagyn
Bagabandy said Tuesday that he believes relations between Mongolia
and China will develop further in the new century.
</P>
<P>
Bagabandy made the statement during a meeting with Ye Xuanping,
visiting Vice-Chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
He said relations between both countries have developed since
the signing of the Sino-Mongolian friendly and cooperation treaty
in 1994, and the heads of both countries have visited each other's
country successfully over the last two years.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his thanks for China's aid to Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Ye said China attaches great importance to its
ties with Mongolia, and China and Mongolia should always be good
neighbors, friends and partners.
</P>
<P>
Ye is on a four-day visit to Mongolia starting on August 15.
</P>
</TEXT>
