<HEADLINE> Activity of "International Friendship Month" Starts in Shenyang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Shenyang 2000 International
Friendship Month started in this capital of northeast China's
Liaoning Province today with a big celebration.
</P>
<P>
During the "friendship month," which will last until the end of
September, the city will have a series of activities such as
celebrations for the 2,300th anniversary of the city's founding,
Chinese Calligraphy and Painting Art Festival and the Second China
Shenyang Trade Fair.
</P>
<P>
A group of national and international events, which include
2000 China (Shenyang) Agricultural Expo, the Fourth Meeting of
East Asian Science Parks, the 2000 Shenyang International Economic
and Trade Fair and the Sixth Plenary Session of Women from
Southeast Asia and Far-east Regions, will also be held at the same
the time of the city's month-long event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
