<HEADLINE> Two Missing After Helicopter Crash in Persian Gulf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Two Iranians went missing after a
helicopter they were aboard crashed Tuesday night over the Persian
Gulf, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter was on its way from an oil platform in the Gulf
to Kish Island, in Iran's southern province of Hormozgan, when it
crashed at an area 60 kilometers west of the island, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
According to the public relations office of Kish free trade
zone, the helicopter with five people on board crashed around 2300
local time (1830 GMT) due to unspecific reasons.
</P>
<P>
The pilot and co-pilot of the helicopter are missing but three
other people were rescued. 
</P>
