<HEADLINE> Jordanian PM's Visit to Syria to Upgrade Bilateral Ties: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The upcoming visit to Syria by
Jordanian Prime Minister Ali Abu Ragheb will further strengthen
bilateral ties in all fields, particularly on issues of water and
economic cooperation, said a senior Jordanian official here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ragheb is expected to visit Syria on Thursday to co-chair a
meeting of the higher joint committee between the two countries
with his Syrian counterpart Mohammed Mustafa Miro, said Jordanian
Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Prime Ministry Affairs Saleh
Irsheidat at a press briefing.
</P>
