accession to the throne in February, 1999, reflect Jordan's
keenness to boost inter-Arab ties and to forge a comprehensive Arab
unity.
</P>
<P>
Ties between Jordan and Syria are improving steadily as Abdullah
has established close ties with Syria's new President Bashar al-
Assad.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have also tided over years of tensions over
Jordan's 1994 peace treaty with Israel as Syria has stood against
any unilateral Arab effort to make peace with the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
In a goodwill gesture, Syria will provide some 3.5 million cubic
meters of drinking water to Jordan this summer though it itself has
been hit by a prevailing drought in the region. 
