rate since November 1975, based on the number of people claiming
benefit.
</P>
<P>
However, average earnings grew by 4.1 percent in June, its
lowest rate for three years. This compares with 4.6 percent in May.
</P>
<P>
Observers here believe that together, the two sets of data can
be taken as reducing the chances of further rises in interest
rates in the near future. 
