situation in Burundi at a time when the 15-nation body called upon
all parties to the conflict in Burundi to end hostilities "without
delay."
</P>
<P>
The council stressed the importance of resuming development
aid to the war-torn central African country.
</P>
<P>
The closed-door council session coincided with the meeting
between President Pierre Buyoya of Burundi and former South
African President Nelson Mandela in South Africa. Buyoya arrived
