saying that council members strongly supported Mandela's
facilitation efforts, and urging the parties to engage seriously
in the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Council members also supported the holding of a donors
conference which would facilitate the relaunching of the Burundian
economy, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
More than 200,000 people, mostly civilians, have died in the
seven-year civil war between the army and the Hutu rebels. Neither
the Burundian government nor the rebels have accepted a peace plan
put forward earlier this month by mediator Mandela to end the war.
