<P>
Of the figure, the value of projects signed with the Japanese
Bank for International Cooperation accounted for 62.5 percent, and
those with the Asian Development Bank, 12.3 percent, and the World
Bank, 13.8 percent, according to Vietnam's Ministry of Planning
and Investment.
</P>
<P>
In the period under review, Vietnam disbursed more than one
billion U.S. dollars, a year-on-year increase of 15 percent. Of
this sum, 85 percent was loans and the remainder, non-refundable
aid.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam plans to disburse 1.68 billion U.S. dollars this year,
about 330 million U.S. dollars more than last year.
</P>
<P>
Since Vietnam resumed credit relations with international
donors in 1993, donors have pledged to provide a total ODA sum of
more than 15 billion U.S. dollars to the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
