<HEADLINE> Hundreds Hospitalized for Food Poisoning in Phnom Penh Factory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of Cambodian garment
factory workers have been hospitalized in five private hospitals
for suspected food poisoning since Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Many workers began vomiting and fainting after eating food that
might have been contaminated, Sok Lakhena, deputy cabinet
director for Phnom Penh Municipality, said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"At least 600 workers were sent to hospitals yesterday," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The incident happened at around 2 a.m. (local time) Tuesday
about half an hour after a break for a meal of rice and noodle
soup, said a staff of Singapore's Suntex Pte. Ltd. garment factory
in the outskirts of Phnom Penh.
</P>
<P>
The factory is employing about 2,500 workers in four shifts.
</P>
<P>
Health officials are examining the cause of the incident and a
conclusion is yet to be made. 
