<HEADLINE> French Press Questions Future of Concorde </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The French press Wednesday
expressed their pessimism about the future of the Concorde
supersonic aircraft after the British Airways suspended the flight
of such planes on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The daily Liberation published a story with the title "
Concorde Bye Bye" saying that the suspension of Concorde by both
British Airways and Air France is "euthanasia" for the plane.
</P>
<P>
The daily Le Figaro said in its title of the Concorde story
that "Will Concorde ever fly again ?" and the daily Le Parisien
said that the suspension of Concorde by British Airways "can
signal the end of the supersonic."
</P>
<P>
The daily L'Humanite said in its title: "Concorde nailed down
at the end of the runway."
</P>
<P>
British Airways Wednesday suspended the flying certificate of
Concorde, three weeks after the crash of the Air France Concorde
near Paris on July 25. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
