<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Fund Market Down on Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 16 (Xinhua) -- China's securities investment
fund market changed its recent corrective attempts and fell across
the board as investors were reluctant to delay profit-taking.
</P>
<P>
However, the downside potential was rather limited as it is
almost certain that buying interest will be attracted to the 22
discounted funds to take advantage of their low prices, according
to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and securities
advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Also there is a fundamental support for the fund market as some
insurance companies are allowed to raise their investment
proportions in securities funds.
</P>
<P>
The Pacific Antai Insurance Co., with its background related to
some foreign parties, recently got the green light from the China
Securities Regulatory Commission (CSRC) to increase their
securities fund investment ratio from 5 to 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
Other applicants are still waiting for CSRC's permission.
</P>
</TEXT>
