<HEADLINE> China's Religious Delegation to Attend Millennium World Peace Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 16 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese religious delegation
will attend the Millennium World Peace Summit of Religious and
Spiritual Leaders to be held in the United States on August 28-31.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, consisting of seven main leaders of Buddhism,
Daoism, Islamism, Catholicism and Christianity, is a peace and
friendship envoy from China, said Wang Zhaoguo, deputy chairman of
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), today.
</P>
<P>
In response to the the coming summit, a seminar about world
peace started today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Wang said that all these religious leaders have a deep
understanding of maintaining world peace. Over 100 million Chinese
are religious, and China's Constitution and laws guarantee their
freedom in religious belief.
</P>
<P>
Wang hopes the delegation will play an active role in the
summit and make contributions to human peace.
</P>
<P>
About 60 representatives from different religious groups and
the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences participated in the seminar.
</P>
