<HEADLINE> Cambodian Leader Arrives in Manila for State Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Prime Minister Hun Sen
arrived here Wednesday for a three-day state visit to boost his
country's ties with the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Executive Secretary Ronaldo Zamora told reporters
that Hun Sen's visit to Manila aims "to forge stronger ties with
the Philippines."
</P>
<P>
The Cambodian prime minister was met by Vice President Gloria
Arroyo, Foreign Secretary Domingo Siazon and Energy Secretary
Mario Tiaoqui.
</P>
<P>
The two sides are expected to sign agreements or memorandums of
understanding on human resources, health and the waiving of visas
for bearers of diplomatic and official passports.
</P>
<P>
According to Zamora, the Cambodian government delegation led by
Hun Sen is also set to go to a rice research institute in Los
Banos,Laguna Province, some 30 kilometers south of Manila, and
then to the Subic Bay Free Port Zone.
</P>
<P>
The Cambodian delegation includes Minister of Foreign Affairs
and International Cooperation Hor Namhong,Minister of Council Sok
An, Minister of Health Hong Sunhuot,Minister of Trade Cham Prasidh
and other senior officials.
</P>
<P>
The Cambodian delegation is to pay a state visit to Brunei
after the Philippines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
