<HEADLINE> Philippine Trade Surplus Rises in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 16 (Xinhua) - The Philippines' merchandise trade
surplus rose to 916 million U.S. dollars in June from 186 million
dollars during the same period last year, the government said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In a press release issued here, the National Statistics Office(
NSO) said, however, that imports fell 6.6 percent in the same
month to 2.494 billion dollars from 2.671 billion dollars last
year.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the NSO said the country's exports increased by 19.4
percent in June to 3.41 billion dollars, compared with 2.857
billion dollars in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
In the first semester, the merchandise trade surplus reached a
total of 2.28 billion dollars, from 686 million dollars a year
earlier.
</P>
<P>
Also, imports for the first half rose 1.5 percent to 15.336
billion dollars from 15.116 billion dollars in the same period
last year,while exports went up 11.5 percent to 17.616 billion
dollars from 15.802 billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
