<HEADLINE> Death Toll Rises to 22 in Kampala Petrol Fire  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The death toll of a petrol fire
accident, which occurred at the Masaka road in the Ugandan capital
Kampala on Monday, has risen to 22 after three more victims died
at hospital.
</P>
<P>
The police confirmed here Wednesday that 19 people were burnt
to death Monday and three others have so far died at hospital.
</P>
<P>
The fire is believed to have been sparked off by somebody who
lit a cigarette while others were scooping oil spilled from a fuel
tanker that was overturned on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Ten of the victims who were rushed to hospital Monday are still
in critical conditions.
</P>
<P>
The fire, which was put out on Monday evening by the Kampala
Fire Brigade, destroyed over 2,000 square meters of a papyrus
swamp. 
</P>
</TEXT>
