<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0810 GMT, August 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE -- Slovak President Rudolf Schuster returned to Slovakia
from Austria on Tuesday after partly recovering from life-
threatening complications, news report reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The 66-year-old president, who received 48-day emergency and
life-saving treatment in Austria, looked weak but was in good
spirit. Schuster was hospitalized on June 14 with ruptured
intestine and was rushed on June 28 to Austria after developing
complications following a surgery in his country. (Slovakia-
President)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- France said on Tuesday that the hostage crisis in the
Philippines has clearly come to an important moment and the French
government is intensifying efforts to secure the release of the
hostages.
</P>
<P>
The French Foreign Ministry made the statement without
mentioning the mediation of Libya between the Philippine
government and the Muslim rebels who are keeping 14 people in
captivity. Three French nationals are among the hostages who are
being kept on the island of Jolo in southern Philippines. (France-
Philippines-Hostage)
</P>
<P>
