<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Mixed in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed mixed in Tokyo
Wednesday, with the benchmark Nikkei index rising for the fourth
straight trading day.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange gained 57.74 points, or 0.35
percent from Tuesday's close to end at 16,356.03.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index which covers all
First Section issues, however, dropped 4.87 points or 0.32 percent
to 1,495.44.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section increased to 524.87 million
shares from Tuesday's 475.45 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Toshiba was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
High-tech issues drew buying after New York's Nasdaq composite
index rose for the third straight trading day Tuesday, closing at
3,851.66, up 1.97 points.
</P>
<P>
Gainers included the mining, paper and brokerage sectors, while
the real estate, marine transportation and retail sectors faced
selling.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers outpaced
gainers 685 to 529, with 171 issues remaining unchanged. 
</P>
