<HEADLINE> Construction of Tourism Facilities Begins in Poverty-sticken Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, August 16 (Xinhua) -- China has started to build
tourism facilities in Guyuan Prefecture of west China's Ningxia
Hui Autonomous Region as an effort by the central government to
help poverty-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
Seven million yuan will be used in developing the Liupanshan
tourism district with an area of over 110 square kilometers as the
Central Government's efforts to help Guyuan, a prefecture that had
just got enough food and clothing for the local people in 1999.
</P>
