<HEADLINE> Sales by Asia's Top Passenger Car Plant to Increase By 70 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Sales revenue by the
Changchun Railway Passenger Car Plant, the largest one in Asia,
are expected to increase by nearly 70 percent to 3 billion yuan (
361 million U.S. dollars) this year.
</P>
<P>
Liu Jingfang, vice-director of the plant, said the plant
expected to sell 1,600 railway passenger cars, a record high and
one third more than its average annual sales.
</P>
<P>
 The plant expanded its capacity of producing 1,200 railway
passenger cars annually this year to meet surging domestic demands
for the cars.
</P>
<P>
 The total sales volume for last year was 1.78 billion yuan (
214 million U.S. dollars), Liu said.
</P>
<P>
 The plant is also capable of producing 160 subway passenger
cars annually, and fixing 300 railway and subway passenger cars
each year.
</P>
<P>
 Subway passenger cars are being used in subway systems in
Beijing, Teheran, the capital of Iran, and several other cities.
</P>
</TEXT>
