<HEADLINE> Manila Stocks Fall Amid Weak Peso </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Share prices at the Philippine
Stock Exchange ended lower Wednesday on concerns over the
weakening peso.
</P>
<P>
The 30-company Phisix, the market's main index, shed 0.21
points to close at 1,473.07.
</P>
<P>
Also, the broader all-share index fell 1.54 points to 656.21.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said most investors stayed at the sidelines, fearing
the peso might breach the crucial level of 45 against one U.S.
dollar in late trading.
</P>
<P>
"The main concern is toward the direction of the peso. There
are also some concerns about the country's macroeconomic figures
like the lower imports in June," Jonas Ravelas, a market analyst
said here.
</P>
<P>
The peso averaged 44.946 early Wednesday, softer compared with
Tuesday's close of 44.915.
</P>
<P>
The government also reported that imports fell 6.6 percent in
June to 2.49 billion dollars, indicating slower manufacturing
activity. 
