<HEADLINE> Japan Sets Conditions for Canceling Zambia's Debt  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the report, this came to light when Etsuya Washio,
president of Rengo, a Japanese trade union federation, and vice-
chairman of International Federation of Trade Unions, held a
joint press briefing with Zambia Congress of Trade Unions (ZCTU)
president Fackson Shamenda in Kitwe in Copperbelt Province.
