<HEADLINE> Ukraine's Trade Grows by 20 Percent in First Half This year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine's foreign trade amounted to
13.027 billion U.S. dollars in the first half of this year, up 20.
2 percent over the same period of 1999, according to the latest
official data published by the State Statistics Committee.
</P>
<P>
Its exports made 6.308 billion dollars in the period, up 18
percent over the year earlier level. Imports hit 6.719 billion, up
22.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The biggest five importers of Ukrainian goods were Russia,
Turkey, USA, Germany and China. Russia was the largest exporter,
followed by Germany, Turkmenistan, Belarus and Italy.
</P>
<P>
The country was reported to have trade relations with more than
170 countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
