<HEADLINE> Four Colombians Die in FARC Incursion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Four Colombians were killed
Tuesday in an incursion by the rebel Revolutionary Armed Forces of
Colombia (FARC) in San Rafael municipality, 102 kilometers east of
Medellin, capital of Antioquia department.
</P>
<P>
The victims were a food store owner, two watchmen and a person
who died of a heart attack, said local authorities Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
During the incursion, guerrillas of FARC's 9th front attacked
police headquarters in San Rafael. They also set fire to a
gasoline station and 27 vehicles.
</P>
<P>
Troops of the army's 4th brigade went to the municipality to
back up police and pursue the guerrillas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
