<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Argentine President
Fernando de la Rua said Tuesday there was no need to devalue the
national currency peso.
</P>
<P>
De la Rua made the remark after former President Carlos Menem
predicted a devaluation after Menem had lunch with entrepreneurs
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The president said, "There's no danger here of devaluation or
of any other crisis or problem."
</P>
<P>
On the cattle disease, de la Rua said that problems resulting
from cattle with foot-and-mouth disease had been overcome.
</P>
