<DOCNO> XIE20000816.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar's Sugar Production Drops in 1999-2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar produced 29,560 tons of
sugar in fiscal year 1999-2000 which ended in March, dropping by
18,838 tons or 38.9 percent compared with the previous fiscal year,
said the country's Central Statistical Organization in its latest
report.
</P>
<P>
The drop in sugar production came after the country had
maintained its average annual sugar output of 50,000 tons for the
past four fiscal years, during which it exported over 35,000 tons
of sugar annually.
</P>
<P>
There are eight state-owned sugar mills in Myanmar, namely
Pyinmana No.1 and 2, Yedashe, Zeyawaddy, Belin, Shwenyaung, Namte
and Kyauktaw.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, three new sugar mills in Bago and Mandalay divisions,
built by the state-run Myanma Sugarcane Enterprise under contracts
with Chinese companies, have successively gone into production
since last December.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Myanmar cultivates over 100,
000 hectares of sugarcane with an annual output of over 5 million
tons.
</P>
<P>
Sugarcane is one of Myanmar's four important pillar crops and
extensive and intensive cultivation of the crop is being made
around the areas of sugar mills for sufficient supply of cane to
the mills. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000816.0226 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S.Lankan Military Confirms 18,000 Tamil Tiger Deaths Since 1982 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Security forces have
confirmed that over 18,000 Tamil Tiger rebels have been killed
since 1982.
</P>
<P>
The military also said that government troops continue to
retake and bring under government control more areas that have
been under the control of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (
LTTE), which has been fighting a war against government forces for
a separate state for 17 years.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics with the Ministry of Defense, quoted
Wednesday by the national news agency "Lankapuwath," 18,262 LTTE
guerrillas have been killed during this period and over 20,000
others wounded.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said that a total of 2,410 Tamil Tiger rebels was
killed in 1999 and 508 killed so far this year.
</P>
<P>
The long-running bloody civil war launched by the LTTE has
claimed more than 60,000 lives.
</P>
<P>
Efforts to achieve a political solution to the war have so far
failed despite three efforts at peace talks under the ruling of
President J.R. Jayewardene in 1984, President Ranasinghe Premadasa
in 1990 and the incumbent President Chandrika Kumaratunga in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Norway has initiated a peace negotiation between the government
and Tamil Tigers but so far little progress has been achieved.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
