<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazilian Police Seize 21 Tons of Marihuana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's Federal Police seized
on Tuesday nearly 21 tons of marihuana pressed into 1.5-kilogram
packages at the border with Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
The drug, which came from Paraguay and was hidden beneath a
load of wooden beams, was found during a routine inspection by
patrols on BR-463 highway in Matto Grosso do Sul state.
</P>
<P>
The policemen, who suspected the excess weight of the load,
found beneath the wood 20,930 kilograms of marihuana covered with
a black plastic canvas.
</P>
<P>
It was the largest seizure of drugs in Brazil in one single
load.
</P>
<P>
This year, Brazil police have confiscated 70 tons of marihuana
mainly produced in the Paraguayan city of Capitan Bado. 
</P>
</TEXT>
