<HEADLINE> Turkey to Send 116-Member Team to Sydney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Turkey is expected to despatch a
116-member delegation to participate in the Sydney Summer Olympic
Games to be held between September 15 and October 1, said the
Anatolia News Agency on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Sources were quoted by the semi-official news agency as saying
on Tuesday that for the first time in the country's sport history,
the Turkish team will include 7 foreign coaches, one foreign
masseur and 10 sportsmen who are Turkish citizens but of foreign
origin.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that Ebru Kavaklioglu, Aksel Mert and Sureyya
Ayhan in athletics, Agasi Agaguloglu, Ramazan Phaliani, Selim
Phaliani and Akin Kuloglu in boxing, Adem Bereket in wrestling,
Selim Tataroglu in judo, and Natalia Nasaridze in archery will
compete with their rivals on behalf of Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The team, to be led by State Minister Fikret Unlu, will leave
for Sydney on September 12 and return to Turkey on October 2.
</P>
</TEXT>
