<HEADLINE> Colombia Edges Uruguay 1-0 at World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Jario "the Tiger" Castillo helped
Colombia beat Uruguay 1-0 Tuesday in a South American Qualifier
for the 2002 World Cup Finals.
</P>
<P>
The game earned the Colombians three points, giving them a
total of 12, three less than division-leading Argentina.
</P>
<P>
The game's lone goal came in the 72nd minute through Castillo
who fired from the right of the box that got past Uruguayan
goaltender Fabian Carini into the net's left corner.
</P>
<P>
Though noticeably slowed by Bogota's altitude, the visiting
team still had several chances to get on the scoresheet before
Castillo's goal.
</P>
<P>
The home team also missed a chance to take a commanding 2-0
lead in the game's 82nd minute when Argentinian referee Daniel
Gimenez awarded Colombia's Gonzalo Martinez a questionable penalty
kick.
</P>
<P>
Colombia will next meet Chile, and Uruguay will meet Ecuador.
</P>
</TEXT>
