<HEADLINE> Chile Upsets Brazil 3-0 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Chile delivered a heavy blow to
Brazil by humiliating the four-time world champions 3-0 Tuesday in
a South American World Cup qualifier.
</P>
<P>
Marcelo Salas became the deciding factor who set up the first
two goals and scored the third himself.
</P>
<P>
Fabian Estay and Ivan Zamorano gave Chile a two-goal halftime
lead while Salas wrapped up the win in the 73rd minute before
being substituted to a standing ovation.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, who had only ever lost one World Cup qualifying match
in their history until last month, have now been beaten in two of
their last three. They lost to Paraguay in July but seemed to have
stopped the rot three weeks ago with a 3-1 win over arch-rivals
Argentina.
</P>
<P>
They dropped to fourth place in the South American World Cup
qualifying group with 11 points from seven games, but could sink
to fifth on Wednesday if Paraguay beat Argentina. Chile are fifth,
with ten points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
