salvage the crumbling Congo peace accord and to pave the way for
the deployment of United nations peacekeepers.
</P>
<P>
The Wall Street Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- Business inventories rose a larger-than-expected 0.9 percent
in June as firms stocked up to keep pace with strong demand. The
small-business index rebounded in July, adding confusion as to
whether economic growth is slowing.
</P>
<P>
