<HEADLINE> France Says Philippine Hostage Crisis at Critical Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 15 (Xinhua) -- France said on Tuesday that the
hostage crisis in the Philippines has clearly come to an important
moment and the French government is intensifying efforts to secure
the release of the hostages.
</P>
<P>
The French Foreign Ministry made the statement without
mentioning the mediation of Libya between the Philippine
government and the Muslim rebels who are keeping 14 people in
captivity.
</P>
<P>
Three French nationals are among the hostages who are being
kept on the island of Jolo in southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Libya has sent a plane to Manila which is waiting to fly to
Jolo to bring the hostages to Tripoli.
</P>
<P>
Three members of a television crew of France 2 channel who were
also taken hostage by the men of Abu Sayyaf are not among the
hostages about to be released, said Agence France-Presse.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-one people were captured by Abu Sayyaf on the Malaysian
island of Sipadan on April 23 and later transferred to Jolo island.
Seven people have been released. 
</P>
