<HEADLINE> Thailand to Step Up Farm Product Promotion in Middle East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Thailand will soon establish
Thai cooperative product distribution centers in some countries in
the Middle East, the Thai News Agency (TNA) reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Director-General of the Cooperative Promotion Department
Boonmee Juntaravong was quoted as saying that the planned
cooperative products distribution centers would be established in
the United Arab Emirates, Saudi Arabia, Bahrain, Oman, Kuwait and
Qatar.
</P>
<P>
The centers, to be managed by a private firm hired by the Thai
Ministry of Agriculture and Cooperatives, would promote and sell
Thai farm products to local consumers, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Thai farm products, to be provided by Thai cooperatives,
would include Thai jasmine or Hom Mali rice, vegetables, and
fruits, the official disclosed.
</P>
<P>
The move will not only boost exports of Thai agricultural
products to overseas markets, but also promote and create networks
between Thai cooperatives and their counterparts in several
countries. 
</P>
