<HEADLINE> Spanish Civil Guards Detonate Car Bomb </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Spanish civil guards Tuesday blew
up a car containing 100 kilograms of explosives, local authorities
said.
</P>
<P>
Civil guards reported that the Renault automobile had been
abandoned Monday afternoon on highway N-230, in the northeastern
province of Huesca.
</P>
<P>
Workers on a nearby farm, who went to offer help, said a woman,
the driver of the car, told them the car was out of order. Half an
hour later, the woman was reportedly picked up by a motorbike.
</P>
<P>
Police ran a check on the car and discovered that it was
transporting dynamite. They sealed off the road, which links the
town of Lerida to France, and carried out a controlled explosion.
</P>
<P>
Police think the car may have been left there by the militant
Basque separatist group ETA.
</P>
<P>
Spain has seen a resurgence of ETA car bombings over the past
few week. Three car bombings that occurred last month in Madrid,
the northern province of Basque, and the southern province of
Malaga, left 10 people injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
