<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Slovak President Rudolf Schuster
returned to Slovakia from Austria on Tuesday after partly
recovering from life-threatening complications, news report
reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The 66-year-old president, who received 48-day emergency and
life-saving treatment in Austria, looked weak but was in good
spirit.
</P>
<P>
