and was rushed on June 28 to Austria after developing
complications following a surgery in his country.
</P>
<P>
With tears in eyes, Schuster kneeled and kissed the ground
after getting off the airplane as he returned to Bratislava,
capital of Slovakia. He was greeted by Prime Minister Mikulas
Dzurinda and other government and legislative leaders.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that after a brief stay in the capital, he will
go to his hometown, Kosice to receive recuperative treatment.
