<HEADLINE> Indonesian Female Lifters Want to Do Big at Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia has a good chance to
win a medal in the women's 48 kilograms class at the Olympic Games
in Sydney next month.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian Olympic Games deputy chef de mission Imron Z.S.
said the absence of Chinese lifters, who won the event at the
World Championships last year, might enable Indonesia's two
lifters Sri Indriyani and Lisa Rumbewas to win the medal.
</P>
<P>
Both Sri and Lisa joined their compatriots Winarni and Supeni,
who are competing in the 53kg divisions, for the final evaluation
onAugust 9 and 14.
</P>
<P>
"As the Chinese lifters will be absent in the women's 48kg
division, our lifters will have a great chance to contribute a
medal from a sport other than badminton," he was quoted by the
Jakarta Post Wednesday as saying.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia earned three Olympic berths but the Indonesian
Weighlifting, Powerlifting and Bodybuilding Association (PABBSI)
had problems in deciding which athletes would represent the
country in theevent. Therefore the association decided to stage an
evaluation topick three athletes.
</P>
<P>
The evaluation results were as follows: Sri lifted 85.5 kgs in
snatch, 112 kgs in clean and jerk and a total lift of 197.5 kgs.
Hertotal lift equaled the world record created by Liu Xiuhua of
China at the World Weightlifting Championships in Montreal in June.
</P>
<P>
While Lisa lifted 85 kgs in snatch, 110 kgs in clean and jerk
and atotal of 195 kgs.
</P>
<P>
In the 53 kg division, Winarni lifted 97.5 kgs, which also
equaledthe world record created by Meng Xianjuan of China in the
World Weightlifting Championships last year. The Indonesian lifted
115 kgsin clean and jerk and a total lift of 212.5 kgs.
</P>
<P>
While Supeni only lifted 85 kgs in snatch, 110 kgs in clean
andjerk and a total lift of 195 kg.
</P>
<P>
Indonesian officials held a meeting on Tuesday to decide which
athletes would represent the country in the quadrennial event.
</P>
<P>
"I will report the results of the meeting to the Olympics
executive training director tomorrow (Wednesday). It's unethical
if I announcethe names today (Tuesday)," Imron said, declining to
mention thelifters.
</P>
<P>
However, he added, the National Sports Council will not
onlyobserve the
final evaluation of the athletes but also assess theirphysical and
psychological condition as well as their self confidence,all of
which are needed to overcome pressure in such a major event.
</P>
</TEXT>
