<HEADLINE> Lewis to Fight Tua in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Lennox Lewis will defend his
two titles against Samoan David Tua on November 11, the British
champion's promoter said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
But the venue choice between Las Vegas or Toronto is yet to be
taken, said Donald Tremblay, of New Jersey-based Main Events.
</P>
<P>
Lewis is the champion of the World Boxing Council and the
International Boxing federation, two of the three major
sanctioning groups of boxing. Lewis surrendered his World Boxing
Association (WBA) crown rather than comply with its order to fight
little-known Johnny Ruiz.
</P>
