<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rios Eliminated from RCA Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Eighth-seeded Marcelo Rios
retired with a recurring groin injury on Tuesday, becoming the
biggest casualty so far of the RCA Championships ATP Tour hard-
court tournament at Indianapolis.
</P>
<P>
Rios, who had reached the tournament's third round in each of
the past three years, lost the first set to Xavier Malisse of
Belgium 6-4 and was unable to continue in the second round of the
870,000 U.S. dollars tournament.
</P>
<P>
Unseeded Vince Spadea, the tournament runner-up last year, fell
at the first hurdle, losing 3-6, 6-3, 6-4 to Vladimir Voltchkov,
the player from Belarus who reached the semifinals at Wimbledon.
</P>
<P>
Seeded players who advanced were No. 2 Yevgeny Kafelnikov of
Russia, No. 10 Wayne Ferreira of South Africa and No. 13 Karim
Alami of Morocco.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov needed just 42 minutes to beat Mikael Tillstrom of
Sweden 6-2, 6-1. Ferreira ousted Arnaud DiPasquale of France 6-4,
6-2, while Alami defeated Cyril Saulnier of France 6-4, 3-6, 7-5.
</P>
</TEXT>
