<HEADLINE> Canada to Send 309 Athletes to Sydney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The Canadian Olympic Committee
announced today that they will send a total of 309 athletes to
compete at the Sydney Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Kayaker Caroline Brunet, 31, a three-time K-1 world champion
and 1996 Olympic gold medal winner, was chosen to carry the
Canadian flag in the Opening Ceremonies at Sydney. She is one of
Canada's top medal hopes at the Games. The Canadian delegation
include 151 male athletes.
</P>
<P>
Reigning Olympic 100m champion Donovan Bailey heads the
athletics roster, with 100m specialist Bruny Surin set to compete
despite not running at the Canadian Olympic trials last weekend.
</P>
