<HEADLINE> Nigeria Vows to Admit More Women in Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian Minister of Co-operation
and Integration in Africa Dapo Sarumi said on Thursday that the
government will leave more posts for women in the country.
</P>
<P>
The News Agency of Nigeria quoted Sarumi as saying that the
involvement of more women in politics would hopefully bring sanity
to the nation's political system.
</P>
<P>
The minister made the remarks in Nigeria's capital Abuja while
receiving Nigerian women rights leader Zainab Maina, who was
recently appointed the co-ordinator for Anglophone Africa for the
International Council for Women.
</P>
<P>
"We are proud of women in the continent, especially in Nigeria,
where women have demonstrated their intellectual prowess in
various fields and any government attempts to ignore them in its
development plan will be doing so at its peril," he said. 
