<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Calls for Improvement of Infrastructure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni said that African countries have no choice but to
industrialize, calling for the improvement of macro economy and
building of infrastructure so that investors can be attracted to
come and do business in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Museveni made the remarks when meeting with six visiting
British Members of Parliament led by Tony Worthington at the State
House in the capital Kampala Thursday afternoon, according to a
press release from the President's Office.
</P>
<P>
The president said the essence of debt relief is to enable
governments of the developing countries to build infrastructure
such as roads and schools.
</P>
<P>
Another way of helping African countries to develop is to
enable them to have access to European markets where they can
export their agricultural produce, said Museveni. 
</P>
