<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US, Rwanda to Enhance Cooperation of Universities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 17 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. government has
disbursed 2 million U.S. dollars to support partnerships between
American and Rwandan Universities in the fields of public health
education and agricultural research and development, according to
reports reaching here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"The 2 million dollars to be made available this fiscal year
will further support the established partnerships in public health
education with the National University of Rwanda and will assist
in improving paramedical training at the Kigali Health Institute,"
a communique from the American Embassy said.
</P>
<P>
The money will also be used to launch a new program called the
"Partnership for Enhancing Agriculture in Rwanda through Linkages
(PEARL)".
</P>
<P>
Under the PEARL program, Michigan State University will form a
partnership with the National University of Rwanda and the
Institute of Science and Agricultural Research in the southern
Butare District to upgrade the curriculum and the level of
agricultural research.
</P>
<P>
It will also develop curricula that provide schools, leaders
and small rural entrepreneurs with practical training in farming,
agricultural processing and marketing technologies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
