<DOCNO> XIE20000816.0284 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angola to Tighten Control Over Diamond Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 17 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan government is
determined to tighten its control over the country's diamond
production and trade with the approval of a protocol on fighting
the illicit trafficking of diamonds and the proposal of
reinforcing the auditing work in the diamond-producing and
commercializing sectors, an official document said here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the document, the Standing Committee of the
Angolan Council of Ministers said on Wednesday that the protocol
between Angola and Belgium is aimed at obtaining technical
assistance and adequate consultancy in the area of
commercialization and a major involvement of the international
community in the fight against the illicit diamond-trafficking.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, the council of ministers said that the
auditing work in the diamond-producing and commercializing sectors
will also be promoted, saying that the work will be executed by
firms of internationally recognized authority, mining societies
and associations in cooperation with the Angolan Diamonds Company
(Endiama).
</P>
<P>
The independent audits to the companies of the diamond
production in the country will verify the companies in compliance
with the fiscal and contract terms and the fulfilment of the
foreign exchange regulations on the part of the companies of the
mining sector and the justification of the debts attributed to the
Endiama.
</P>
<P>
The committee also paid much attention to the rehabilitation of
the diamond production in the country. One of the memorandums
recommends the new operating forms of the Endiama, with an aim to
make it an important instrument for fomenting and regulating of
the diamond activity.
</P>
<P>
The memo defines the ways in which the small and medium-scale
producers should operate so that the state can have a growing
control of the sector and benefit from its output. 
</P>
</TEXT>
