<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 17 (Xinhua) -- The fuel supply situation has
remained critical in Zimbabwe with most service stations reported
to have dried up while only a few that still have limited supplies
experienced long queues of motorists, The Herald reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman for the Oil Industry Tom Walter said: "The overall
fuel supply is extremely critical countrywide," adding that there
will be "frequent stock-outs at service stations."
</P>
<P>
