situation in Zimbabwe is now extremely critical.
</P>
<P>
There will be frequent stock-outs at service stations and that
car owners should be patient and courteous when they meet with
long queues for fuel, it said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The country has been experiencing an acute shortage of foreign
currency since December last year to import fuel. At least 14
million U.S. dollars is needed every month to acquire enough
supplies to meet the country's fuel needs. 
