Jackson Memorial Hospital in Miami where he died of his injuries.
This is the first such shooting incident to involve a staff member
of MICAH in Haiti.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the shooting, the Council called on the government
of Haiti to carry out a speedy inquiry into the incident and to
bring those responsible to justice without delay.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations has expressed its deep concern at the
alarming law and order situation in the country in recent days.
