<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hezbollah Calls for Eliminating Sectarianism in Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Hezbollah, or Party of God backed
by Syria and Iran, has announced its election platform which
stresses the elimination of sectarianism from the Lebanese
political system, local media reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah Deputy leader Sheikh Naim Kassem, speaking at a news
conference on Tuesday, said the platform calls for the formation of
a national committee to recommend steps for the elimination of
political sectarianism, which was proposed in the 1989 Taif Accord,
the Arab-
brokered agreement that put an end to Lebanon's 15-year civil war.
</P>
<P>
Kassem also told reporters the names of Hezbollah's candidates
for the elections in Beirut, north Lebanon, the Bekaa and south
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The party's platform said the next government will be urged to
carry out a comprehensive development plan for the "liberated
areas" in the southern and western Bekaa, while the party itself
will continue its efforts to ensure the release of Lebanese
prisoners held in Israeli jails.
</P>
<P>
The party will "resist normalization" of ties with Israel and
refuse to coexist with the Zionist invaders, said the platform,
adding Hezbollah will also oppose the settlement of Palestinian
refugees on Lebanese soil and "insist on their return to their
homes in the whole of Palestine."
</P>
<P>
The party reaffirmed its "continued hostility" to the United
States, "which favors and supports the Zionist entity". It
considers the Lebanese-Syrian alliance as "a source of strength to
both countries."
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah's platform calls for administration reforms to combat
corruption, a fair solution to the problem of the displaced, and
a new election law.
</P>
<P>
The parliament election will be held at the end of August. Some
128 legislators will be picked up from candidates. Hezbollah has
nine seats in the current parliament which has the power to approve
the nomination of prime minister and the formation of government.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000816.0314 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt Welcomes U.S. Order to Step up Inspection of Boeing 767 Elevator </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Transport Minister Ibrahim
el-Demiri on Wednesday welcomed an order by the U.S. Federal
Aviation Administration (FAA) to step up inspection of Boeing 767
elevator control systems, calling it a positive sign for the probe
into last year's EgyptAir crash.
</P>
<P>
The investigations, demanded by the Egyptian side last February,
are developing "in a good direction," el-Demiri told reporters upon
return to Cairo from the United States.
</P>
<P>
The minister was commenting on an upcoming "emergency
airworthiness directive" by the FAA, which will increase inspection
requirements for the system that controls the Boeing 767's
elevators.
</P>
<P>
The investigation has started to address various technical
aspects and this is "in our interests," he said, warning against
making premature judgements on the causes of the crash which killed
217 people.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian investigators have for months been asking their U.S.
counterparts to further investigate the possibility that a failure
of the elevator control system caused EgyptAir Flight 990 to crash
into the Atlantic shortly after take-off from New York airport on
October 31.
</P>
<P>
The two elevators located on the tail of a plane control the
upward or downward movement of the aircraft's nose.
</P>
<P>
FAA spokesman Les Dorr said on Wednesday the inspection
directive for Boeing 767s will be published soon. But he added the
decision was not linked to the EgyptAir crash or any other
incident.
</P>
<P>
But the Egyptian transport minister said the inspection order
has effectively rendered void accusations that an Egyptian pilot
deliberately crashed the plane into the Atlantic.
</P>
<P>
Some U.S. investigators suspect the relief co-pilot of EgyptAir
Flight 990, Gameel al-Battouti, downed the plane in an act of
suicide, according to leaks from the probe. Cairo has strongly
opposed the theory.
</P>
<P>
El-Demiri has been in the United States where he attended the
publication last week of 1,665 pages of factual reports related to
the crash. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000816.0315 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank of Canada Forecasts Higher Economic Growth Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Canada's central bank forecast a
higher rate of 4.75 percent Wednesday than its May prediction of 4.
5 percent for the country's economic growth this year.
</P>
<P>
Bank of Canada Governor Gordon Thiessen declared a positive "
outlook for Canadian economic growth and inflation" in a statement,
reaffirming "economic activity in Canada remains strong" while
signs begin to show an economic slowdown in the United States.
</P>
<P>
The bank based its prediction on the report that growth
continued being strong at 3.5 to 4.25 percent with the core
inflation dropping to 1.4 percent in June.
</P>
<P>
"This suggests that demand may not yet have outstripped Canada'
s production capacity," according to the bank.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Thiessen cautioned about economic uncertainties
including the possibility of rising inflation pressures in the
United States in the second half of the year.
</P>
<P>
The bank expects the U.S. Federal Reserve may have to further
raise interest rates in case the economy continues to be hot to
build up inflation pressure.
</P>
<P>
"Yes, there are some signs of slowing. But I think it's too
soon to say that we've really gotten the momentum of the U.S.
economy to a sustainable pace," Thiessen said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
